Andrew N. Liveris, Dow's chairman and CEO, expressed support for President Obama's American Jobs Act and his focus on trade and infrastructure. Liveris believes that opening access to foreign markets and adopting free trade agreements, along with investing in the nation's infrastructure, are crucial for creating quality jobs and revitalizing the manufacturing sector. He urges Congress to swiftly consider and implement aspects of the proposal that will have the greatest immediate impact on boosting the economy and creating jobs.